.TH git-daft-repo-add 1  "git-daft-repo-add 1.23.1" 
.SH NAME
git\-daft\-repo\-add \- Register a repository in the repo catalog
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgit\-daft\-repo\-add\fR [\fB\-\-name\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIPATH\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Registers a repository in daft\*(Aqs repo catalog — the machine\-local registry
behind cross\-repo commands like `git daft go <repo>` and `git daft repo list`.
.PP
The catalog is normally maintained automatically: cloning, initializing, or
running any daft command inside a repo keeps its entry current. Reach for
`repo add` to register a repository daft has never operated in, or to rename
an entry with \-\-name.
.PP
Names must be unique among live entries. Automatic registration resolves
collisions by suffixing (`api\-2`); an explicit \-\-name that is already taken
is an error instead.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-name\fR \fI<NAME>\fR
Catalog name for the repo; renames it when already registered
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress progress reporting
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIPATH\fR]
Repository to register (default: the repo containing the current directory)
.SH VERSION
v1.23.1
